                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/09/2003&nbsp;: 5:39:58 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Well I have a 65 shaman and have pled several twinks and I really disagree with most of it.  First you want to be 63+ so you can give group regen to your twink.<br /><br />Next proceed directly to padual.  Do not hunt in any newbie zone ... you want to be on padual shadeweaver side.  Since the mobs are red to you at this level the shaman needs to cripple them.  Once crippled you and pet will tear through them.  With the regen on you shaman wont need to heal you.  you will get to level 10 within an hour ... no damage shield needed.<br /><br />As the muck guys start turning darkblue start doing fiends.  Dont worry about curing the crud till you are ready to leave.  You will just get reinfected and with regen it doesnt matter.<br /><br />At level 15ish move to bandits.  Stay there till 24 ... even though these are blue mobs to you in the 20s the exp is worth it.<br /><br />Once you ding 24 I like to move to nurga.  I have only done this with mellees at this level but the exp rocked.  It was as fast as padual for exp.  The big key is to have shaman cripple slow and malosinia the mobs.<br /><br />Exp started to slow done from an insane pace in the mid 30s.  35ish to 46 maybe try com or lguk.  Once you ding 49 I would head to poj.  Rats, guards and prisoners are like 46-48 and give great exp.  Killing the mobs guarding mauvin(sp?) is great exp but a bit tougher to hold.</span></font></td>
